    "note": "Form applicability (who can/cannot use ITR-1/2/3/4) cross-checked against current AY 2026-27 ITR-form reporting and the CBDT-notified form changes. ITR-1 now allows Section 112A LTCG up to Rs 1.25 lakh when no capital loss is carried forward, but this tool conservatively routes detected capital-gains uploads to ITR-2 because broker uploads can include disqualifying STCG/loss details. Due dates are separated by profile: most non-audit individual/ITR-2 paths use 31-Jul-2026; non-audit business/professional ITR-3 paths use 31-Aug-2026; audit paths use 31-Oct-2026. Confirm against the e-filing portal before filing."
